subSubSection.paragraph:
Of the new species described here, 

P. incomposita


sp. nov.

is the only one with abundant giant diactines (that are never organized in tufts) projecting through its surface. Moreover, it is the only species with tangential triactines on its surface, and with an atrial skeleton composed exclusively of tetractines. The choanoskeletal composition (number of spicule categories, and their size and shape; 

Figure 
4

; 

Tables 
1-3

) also differs between these three new species.
